“I learned to dance in the rain”

💭Knew this wall was meant for me when I walked by it. Must’ve been the fading paint, rigid surface, the type of wall you walk by and don’t even notice… but my words have the tenacity of pushing through anything, because I believe in them… and the results are always beautiful.

This is my first poem of the year, and in a while. And if I’m being honest with all of you, I’ve felt the weight of these words for a while now. Maybe I don’t need the conversations in order to know what the world is feeling too, what it’s going through, and most of all what it’s lacking.

Just like my other words… it was finally time to release these, and share them. Let others heal through them, share the hope these words envelope, let others know I’ve been lost too, and I’ve learned just like you to make it through the rain.

I admire you for not just trying, but learning… and sometimes it takes a lot of rearranging to get back on track with where you want to be, who you want to be, and to genuinely be happy… but I believe in you, and you can count on me on a rainy day🤍

👑I’m back NYC… I’ve left parts of my Soul everywhere along the way, but home is where I’m needed, so this is where I’ll be… for now.

Only yours,

“Don’t give up on your happiness”

💭I’ve kept these words to myself all of last year, my goal is happiness, to remain hopeful, to be daring enough to be myself whether there’s 50 thousand of you following or just me alone.

7SoulsDeep was created for me. Not to cater to or fiddle with clout and fame in this industry as I never cared for art prior to this, but because I wasn’t afraid of risking for my freedom(both literal and figuratively speaking), some out of necessity others with only the intention of creating the space that would allow me to be.

🖍️This space I created, this energy and feeling you get from my words… that’s the feeling I had to give myself when I lost it all, when I needed someone and no one was there, when I thought I wasn’t beautiful enough, when I attempted and failed, when i thought I couldn’t push anymore. When I thought depression would get the best of me. When I thought I had to hide the person I was. When you’ve put in all this work to heal, and still hurt. When you feel lost, and needed comfort, needed a friend, needed that push to get up. And for those times they told me I never could, I would never make it at anything in Life… 

Well here I am, and I am far from done.

“It’s you…”

💭I’m here for the long run. I’ve been needing these words, and it always gives me new perspectives… the feeling always seems to run deeper.
Maybe it’s because I understand being under so much on and off lows and needing to be embraced to be understood or damn… maybe just seen.
Because regardless of the transitions or pain. 
I’m grateful to be feeling who I am at the pace that I need… right? is that not beautiful that I’m trying to find myself…again? Because I want more healing, no scratch that I want my healing to run deeper than the pain, deeper than any rain, so deep whenever a low moment creeps by I smile because I finally worked through breaking apart everything that kept me down.
And I’ve appreciated those moments of lows, even more now at this moment to create what I love, to write what I need, and painting has been a beautiful way for me to continue to express. To continue to connect to my rawest self, and enjoy myself as well. That alone time is wonderful, my studio time back here in BK… I guess I’ve been a bit selfish, and thank you for sticking around patiently hope we’ve grown together on this journey, and that mine has provoked thoughts and self reflection. As I am going to be releasing some new pieces soon, and projects.
I’ve been spilling my feelings lately… for me, and in return for you. 
I’ve never stopped being raw, or me. I just kept it closer to me…
